      <h4 class="text-danger display-4 text-center pt-4 pb-3 col-md-6 col-10 m-auto" id="resultDisplayScore"></h4> 
      <h4 class="text-light text-center pt-3 pb-3 col-md-6 col-10 m-auto" id="resultDisplayMeaning"></h4>
      <h4 class="text-light text-center pt-3 pb-3 col-md-6 col-10 m-auto" id="resultDisplayComparative"></h4>
      <h4 class="text-light text-center pt-3 pb-3 col-md-6 col-10 m-auto" id="resultDisplayWordList"></h4>
      <h4 class="text-center pt-3 pb-3 col-md-6 col-10 m-auto text-warning" id="resultDisplayPairList"></h4>


      <h2 class="col-md-7 col-10 text-muted text-center m-auto pt-5">Do you agree with system calculation? If yes, please confirm it! Thank you!</h2>
      <div class="text-center m-auto pt-3">
          <button class="text-center p-4 m-auto btn btn-success col-md-3 col-5 d-block" id="buttonAcceptSave">Agree!</button>
      </div>

      <h2 class="col-md-7 col-10 text-muted text-center m-auto pt-5">Don't agree? Please provide your raiting score by choosing from the list and click the button below. Thank you!</h2>

      <div class="col-md-5 col-10 text-center m-auto pt-3">
          <h6 class="text-danger text-center pt-4 pb-3 col-md-10 col-10 m-auto" id="scoreNotProvided"></h6> 
          <div class="input-group">
              <div class="input-group-prepend">
                  <label class="input-group-text bg-dark text-light" for="choosenScore">Options</label>
                </div>
              <select class="custom-select bg-dark text-light" id="choosenScore">
                <option selected>Choose your score from the list...</option>
                <option value="-5">-5 - totaly negative, totaly traumatic or totaly dangerous</option>
                <option value="-4">-4 - very negative, very sad or very traumatic</option>
                <option value="-3">-3 - very negative</option>
                <option value="-2">-2 - negative or sad</option>
                <option value="-1">-1 - quite negative or a little sad</option>
                <option value="0">0 - not negative, not possitive, neutral</option>
                <option value="1">1 - quite possitive or happy</option>
                <option value="2">2 - happy or motivating</option>
                <option value="3">3 - very positive or happy</option>
                <option value="4">4 - very possitive, very happy or very motivating</option>
                <option value="5">5 - totaly positive, totaly happy, totaly motivating</option>
              </select>
            </div>     
      </div>

      <div class="text-center m-auto pt-3">
          <button class="text-center p-4 m-auto d-block btn btn-danger col-md-3 col-5 d-block" id="buttonDeclineSave">Don't agree!</button> 
      </div>



      <h1 class="display-md-3 display-4 text-light text-center m-auto pt-5" id="features" >How Does SentiBlock Works?</h1>
      <h4 class="display-5 text-light text-center m-auto pt-5" id="features" >The Words Adding</h4>
      <p class="col-md-7 col-10 lead text-muted text-center m-auto pt-5">The system allows you to add new words that will be saved into the JSON file together with the score. Words will be later used along with Official AFINN words database to measure the sentimental analysis of provided sentence.</p>
      <h4 class="display-5 text-light text-center m-auto pt-5" id="features" >The Sentimental Analysis</h4>
      <p class="col-md-7 col-10 lead text-muted text-center m-auto pt-5">We use AFIN words database along with custom added words and matching scores. The AFINN-111 - newest version with 2477 words and phrases allows us to measure the sentimental value of specific words groups. Hovewer, AFFIN does not provide all words that we would like to possibly use. That's why SentiBlock allows us to input our custom words and calulate sentimental value using both AFINN and custom list. We encourage you to read more about work of AFINN Finn Ã…rup Nielsen. To read more about AFIN check below</p>
      <div class="text-center m-auto">
        <a href="http://www2.imm.dtu.dk/pubdb/views/publication_details.php?id=6010" class="badge badge-danger m-auto text-center align-middle">AFINN</a>
      </div>
      <h4 class="display-5 text-light text-center m-auto pt-5" id="features" >The Sentimental Analysis Extra Features</h4>
      <p class="col-md-7 col-10 lead text-muted text-center m-auto pt-5">Beyond second words source that was not provided by AFINN, we also coded the part which allows to calculate scores of word pairs. Clean AFINN and singular words are not always the most trusthworthy factors. That's why we created the third source which provides the scores for sentimental analysis for pairs of words containing at least 2 words. Example: "not bad".</p>
      
